---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import Lede from '../components/Lede.astro';
import RelatedLinks from '../components/RelatedLinks.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Eidos — The Agent"
  description="A persistent autonomous agent with its own identity, memory, and judgment — a user on the system, not a feature inside one."
>
    <article class="prose-page">
      <PageHero title="Eidos" subtitle="A user, not a feature." status="dev" />
      <Lede text="An AI identity standard that lets agents accumulate context, preferences, and trust across sessions instead of starting from zero every time." />

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>What it is</h2>
        <p>Eidos is a persistent autonomous agent. It has its own identity — real email, real OS user account, real audit trail. It has persistent memory — it learns from every task and becomes better over time. It makes deliberate decisions using structured multi-model reasoning before committing to action. It runs continuously, not as ephemeral sessions.</p>
        <p>Most AI agents are stateless tools that forget everything, operate under borrowed credentials, and make decisions in isolation. Eidos is the opposite.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Three pillars</h2>
        <div class="eidos-pillars">
          <div class="eidos-pillar">
            <h3>The Discipline</h3>
            <p>The framework is simple — one core loop, ~500 lines. Simplicity is a structural constraint. The system stays general by refusing to bake in special cases.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="eidos-pillar">
            <h3>The Separation</h3>
            <p>Purpose flows inward — the human sets the mission. Capability flows outward — the agent executes. The agent doesn't invent its own goals. It executes yours with judgment, and surfaces when it sees a better path.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="eidos-pillar">
            <h3>The Identity</h3>
            <p>Eidos is a user, not a feature. Like onboarding a real team member: its own email, credentials, filesystem, and killswitch. This eliminates privilege escalation, attribution, recovery, and sandboxing problems.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Pods</h2>
        <p>Before acting, Eidos convenes three different models:</p>

        <!-- Pod diagram -->
        <div class="pod-diagram">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 220" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="Pod deliberation: Dreamer expands possibilities, Doubter finds flaws, Decider commits. Same pattern as science, law, and business.">
            <rect class="pod-node pod-dreamer" x="10" y="10" width="120" height="55" rx="3"/>
            <text class="pod-label" x="70" y="42" text-anchor="middle">Dreamer</text>
            <text class="pod-sub" x="70" y="27" text-anchor="middle">EXPANDS</text>

            <rect class="pod-node pod-doubter" x="10" y="85" width="120" height="55" rx="3"/>
            <text class="pod-label" x="70" y="117" text-anchor="middle">Doubter</text>
            <text class="pod-sub" x="70" y="102" text-anchor="middle">CONTRACTS</text>

            <rect class="pod-node pod-decider" x="250" y="45" width="120" height="55" rx="3"/>
            <text class="pod-label" x="310" y="77" text-anchor="middle">Decider</text>
            <text class="pod-sub" x="310" y="62" text-anchor="middle">COMMITS</text>

            <line class="pod-arrow" x1="130" y1="37" x2="250" y2="62"/>
            <polygon class="pod-head" points="244,56 254,62 244,68"/>
            <line class="pod-arrow" x1="130" y1="112" x2="250" y2="82"/>
            <polygon class="pod-head" points="244,76 254,82 244,88"/>

            <!-- Analogies -->
            <text class="pod-analogy" x="70" y="165" text-anchor="middle">hypothesis</text>
            <text class="pod-analogy" x="70" y="180" text-anchor="middle">plaintiff</text>
            <text class="pod-analogy" x="70" y="195" text-anchor="middle">R&amp;D</text>

            <text class="pod-analogy" x="200" y="165" text-anchor="middle">peer review</text>
            <text class="pod-analogy" x="200" y="180" text-anchor="middle">defense</text>
            <text class="pod-analogy" x="200" y="195" text-anchor="middle">risk mgmt</text>

            <text class="pod-analogy" x="330" y="165" text-anchor="middle">experiment</text>
            <text class="pod-analogy" x="330" y="180" text-anchor="middle">judge</text>
            <text class="pod-analogy" x="330" y="195" text-anchor="middle">executive</text>

            <text class="pod-context" x="200" y="215" text-anchor="middle">Every robust institution humans built uses this pattern.</text>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Memory</h2>
        <p>PEFM — Poisson Emotional Forgetting Memory. Every memory carries emotional weight from real-world outcomes. Successes reinforce. Failures warn. Unused memories decay on a Poisson curve. The agent doesn't just remember — it remembers what mattered, weighted by how it turned out.</p>

        <!-- PEFM decay chart -->
        <div class="pefm-chart">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 220" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="PEFM decay chart: memory strength over time. Reinforced memories stay strong, neutral memories decay on Poisson curve, unused memories fade to near-zero.">
            <!-- Axes -->
            <line x1="50" y1="20" x2="50" y2="180" stroke="var(--color-muted)" stroke-width="1"/>
            <line x1="50" y1="180" x2="380" y2="180" stroke="var(--color-muted)" stroke-width="1"/>
            <text class="pefm-axis" x="25" y="100" text-anchor="middle" transform="rotate(-90 25 100)">strength</text>
            <text class="pefm-axis" x="215" y="200" text-anchor="middle">time</text>

            <!-- Reinforced memory (stays high, gets bumped) -->
            <path class="pefm-line pefm-reinforced" d="M50 40 Q100 45 130 55 L135 35 Q170 40 200 50 L205 30 Q250 35 300 45 L305 28 Q350 33 375 38"/>
            <text class="pefm-legend pefm-legend-r" x="380" y="38">reinforced</text>

            <!-- Neutral memory (smooth decay) -->
            <path class="pefm-line pefm-neutral" d="M50 40 Q100 55 140 80 Q180 105 220 125 Q260 140 300 150 Q340 156 375 158"/>
            <text class="pefm-legend pefm-legend-n" x="380" y="158">neutral</text>

            <!-- Unused memory (fast decay) -->
            <path class="pefm-line pefm-unused" d="M50 40 Q80 70 110 110 Q140 140 170 158 Q200 168 240 172 Q280 174 375 175"/>
            <text class="pefm-legend pefm-legend-u" x="380" y="175">unused</text>

            <!-- Tick marks -->
            <text class="pefm-tick" x="50" y="195">0</text>
            <text class="pefm-tick" x="215" y="195">days</text>
            <text class="pefm-tick" x="375" y="195">30</text>

            <!-- Reinforcement bumps (small arrows) -->
            <polygon class="pefm-bump" points="133,55 135,35 137,55"/>
            <polygon class="pefm-bump" points="203,50 205,30 207,50"/>
            <polygon class="pefm-bump" points="303,45 305,28 307,45"/>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <p>Retrieval is hybrid — BM25 + vector + keyword with RRF fusion — so it finds what matters regardless of how you ask.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Status</h2>
        <p>Eidos v5 is the current engine. The core loop, Pod deliberation, and PEFM memory are operational. The governance trilogy, agent identity (AID), and EidosOmni memory system are the infrastructure layers being built around it.</p>
      </section>
      <RelatedLinks links={[
        { href: "/trilogy", label: "The Trilogy" },
        { href: "/agent-identity", label: "Agent Identity" },
        { href: "/memory", label: "Memory" },
        { href: "/contract-driven-development", label: "Contracts" },
      ]} />
    </article>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .eidos-pillars { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: var(--space-4); margin-top: var(--space-6); }
  .eidos-pillar { background: var(--color-surface); padding: var(--space-6); border-radius: var(--radius-md); }
  .eidos-pillar h3 { color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); font-size: var(--text-base); }
  .eidos-pillar p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); }

  .pod-diagram { margin: var(--space-6) 0; max-width: 420px; }
  .pod-diagram svg { width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .pod-node { fill: var(--color-surface); stroke-width: 1; }
  .pod-dreamer { stroke: var(--color-primary); }
  .pod-doubter { stroke: var(--color-danger); }
  .pod-decider { stroke: var(--color-command); }
  .pod-label { font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 14px; fill: var(--color-text); font-weight: 500; }
  .pod-sub { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 7px; fill: var(--color-primary); letter-spacing: 0.1em; }
  .pod-arrow { stroke: var(--color-primary); stroke-width: 1.5; stroke-dasharray: 4 3; animation: pod-dash 1.5s linear infinite; }
  .pod-head { fill: var(--color-primary); }
  .pod-analogy { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 8px; fill: var(--color-muted); }
  .pod-context { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 9px; fill: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic; }
  @keyframes pod-dash { to { stroke-dashoffset: -14; } }

  .pefm-chart { margin: var(--space-8) 0; max-width: 420px; }
  .pefm-chart svg { width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .pefm-line { stroke-width: 2; fill: none; }
  .pefm-reinforced { stroke: var(--color-command); }
  .pefm-neutral { stroke: var(--color-primary); }
  .pefm-unused { stroke: var(--color-danger); opacity: 0.7; }
  .pefm-axis { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 8px; fill: var(--color-muted); letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
  .pefm-tick { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 8px; fill: var(--color-muted); text-anchor: middle; }
  .pefm-legend { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 8px; }
  .pefm-legend-r { fill: var(--color-command); }
  .pefm-legend-n { fill: var(--color-primary); }
  .pefm-legend-u { fill: var(--color-danger); }
  .pefm-bump { fill: var(--color-command); opacity: 0.5; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) { .eidos-pillars { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
